antile Disorder: the Crisis and Decline of the New Left, London:Routledge & K. Paul, 1977.（二）論文1. 學位論文Chou, Liang-Kai, ‘Modern British Historians and their Conceptions of History,’unpublished Ph. D dissertation, State University of New York at Buffalo, 1993.Holden, David R., ‘The First New Left in Britain, 1956-1962,’ unpublished Ph.D.thesis, University of Wisconsin, Madison, 1976.Howe, Antony, ‘The Past Is Ours: the Political Usage of English History by theBritish Communist Party, and the Role of Dona Torr in the Creation of ItsHistorians’ Group, 1930-56,’ unpublished Ph. D thesis, University of Sydney,2004.Niemi, William L., ‘Popular Politics and Democratic Theory: Democratization inVictorian Britain,’ Ph.D. dissertation, University of California, Los Angeles,1996.Skelly, Colin Brian, ‘The Origins, Nature and Development of Moral Force Chartism,1836-1850,’ Ph.D. thesis, The University of York (United Kingdom), 2005.Taylor, Miles, ‘Radicalism and Patriotism, 1848-1859,’ unpublished Ph. D thesis,University of Cambridge, 1989.2. 一般論文Andrews, Geoff, ‘The Three New Lefts and their Legacies,’ in Geoff Andrews et al.eds. New Left, New Right and Beyond: Taking the Sixties Seriously, Hampshireand New York: Palgrave, 1999, pp. 66-84.Ashman, Sam, ‘The Communist Party Historians’ Group,’ in John Rees ed., Essayson Historical Materialism, London: Bookmarks, 1998, pp.145-160.Bergmann, Gustav, ‘Logical Positivism, Language, and the Reconstruction ofMetaphysics’ (1953), in Richard Rorty ed., The Linguistic Turn: Recent Essays inPhilosophical Method, Chicago: University of Chicago Press, 1967, pp.63-71.Briggs, Asa, ‘The Language of “Class” in Early Nineteenth-Century England,’ in TheCollected Essays of Asa Briggs, Vol. I: Words, Numbers, Places, People, Brighton:Harvester Press, 1985, pp. 3-33.Eley, Geoff, ‘Is All the World a Text?’ in Terrence J. McDonald ed., The Historic Turnin the Human Sciences, Ann Arbor: University of Michigan Press, 1996,pp.