關鍵字(中)
濂洛風雅何基王柏金履祥道統文道合一北山學派


關鍵字(英)
Relation to the Literature and “Dao”Wang-boJin-lu-xiang“Lian luo feng ya”He-jiBei-shan School of Thought


學科別分類
學科別＞人文學＞語言文學



中文摘要
　　從宋代到明代，理學家對文學的態度產生了一些變化。宋代的理學家對文學的態度較為貶抑，但是明代初年的理學家卻同時也是明初重要的文學家。筆者以為這個變化之所以產生，宋末元初之時的理學學派應是十分重要的關鍵。本文便以北山學派為一例子，探討理學家的文、道關係由分而合的變化歷程。 　　北山學派乃是何基所開創的理學學派。何基是黃榦的學生，以篤守師說聞名。他所開創的北山學派歷史悠久，跨越了宋、元、明三代，而且人數眾多，是當時十分重要的朱子學派別。 　　本文探討北山學派如何結合文、道思想，以及如何將文學與道統二者合而為一，以道統體系架構一套符合理學家思想的「文統」架構。筆者以為：想釐清理學史上文、道關係的轉變歷程，北山學派必是一條重要的線索。


英文摘要
　　The Li-xue School of Thought began in the Song Dynasty and in the years leading up to and the Ming Dynasty underwent a dramatic shift in its outlook on literature.  During the Song Dynasty scholars regarded as unimportant and a waste of time, however, from when the Ming Dynasty came into existence, this philosophical perspective had already been dramatically altered; the scholars of the Ming Dynasty regarded literature as something worth studying and during this time produced several important literary works.　　In my research I tried to determine why this paradigm shift regarding literature occurred.  This transformation began in the early days of the Yuan Dynasty, the dynasty after the Song Dynasty and before the Ming Dynasty.  In order to determine what factors caused this change, I looked at the Bei-shan School of Thought, a branch of the Li-xue school of thought.  More specifically, I considered the relationship of the “Dao” to literature.  In the beginning of the Song Dynasty it is clear that literature and the “Dao” were completely separate and existed independently.  When the Yuan Dynasty began, ideas contained in literature started to crossover into the philosophies and beliefs of the “Dao”.  This crossover process continued until the utilization of literature to develop and enhance the teachings of the “Dao.”　　The Bei-shan School of Thought is a branch of the Li-xue School of Thought created by He-ji.   He-ji is infamous for his belief in the teachings of his teachers and regarding their words as the gospel truth.  When creating the Bei-shan school of thought, He-ji based many of his ideas on what he had learned as a student of Huang-gan, one of his former teachers.  This school has a long history stretching over three dynasties, the Song, the Yuan, and the Ming.  Over this time period, the Bei-shan School of Thought has gained many followers and is one of the most important branches of the Zhu-zi School of Thought, also a part of the Li-xue School of Thought. 　　This thesis confers how the Bei-shan School of Thought combines the ideas contained within literature with the philosophies of “Dao”, and merges the literature and “Dao-tong” into a single whole.  This single whole became known as the “Wen-tong” system and is a system that fits well with the Li-xue philosophy.  The Bei-shan School of Thought is an important key to discovering the changing histories of literature and “Dao” and their relationship with one another.                    


